<LegalLayout
  title="Cookie Policy"
  description="Learn about how AUXO Data Labs uses cookies and similar tracking technologies on our website."
  lastUpdated="January 10, 2026"
>
  <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
  <p>
    This Cookie Policy explains how Rapple International FZE (trading as AUXO Data Labs, "we," "us," or "our") uses cookies and similar technologies on our website, auxodata.com ("Site").
  </p>
  <p>
    This policy should be read alongside our <a href={createUrl("legal/privacy-policy")}>Privacy Policy</a>, which explains how we use personal data.
  </p>

  <h2>2. What Are Cookies?</h2>
  <p>
    Cookies are small text files placed on your device (computer, smartphone, or tablet) when you visit a website. They are widely used to make websites work more efficiently, provide a personalized experience, and provide usage information to website owners.
  </p>

  <h2>3. How We Use Cookies &amp; Google Consent Mode v2</h2>
  <p>
    We use cookies to enable essential security, measure Site performance, and manage marketing campaigns.
  </p>
  <h3>Google Consent Mode v2:</h3>
  <p>
    As an analytics consultancy, we implement Google Consent Mode v2. This ensures that Google tags (Analytics and Ads) adjust their behavior based on your consent status.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>If you Consent:</strong> Cookies are stored to track detailed user journeys.</li>
    <li><strong>If you Deny:</strong> We use non-identifying "pings" to model data without storing personal cookies, ensuring privacy compliance with GDPR and UAE PDPL.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Your Choices &amp; Managing Consent</h2>
  <h3>4.1. Consent Banner</h3>
  <p>
    On your first visit, a cookie banner will appear allowing you to:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Accept All:</strong> Allow all cookie categories.</li>
    <li><strong>Reject Non-Essential:</strong> Allow only technically necessary cookies.</li>
    <li><strong>Preferences:</strong> Customize specific categories.</li>
  </ul>
  <h3>4.2. Withdrawing Consent</h3>
  <p>
    You can change your preferences or withdraw consent at any time by clicking the "Cookie Settings" link located in the footer of our website.
  </p>
  <h3>4.3. Browser Settings</h3>
  <p>
    You can also block cookies via your browser settings. However, blocking "Essential Cookies" may cause parts of the Site to break.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Chrome</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://support.apple.com/guide/safari/manage-cookies-and-website-data-sfri11471/mac" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Safari</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/delete-cookies-in-microsoft-edge-63947406-40ac-c3b8-57b9-2a946a29ae09" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Microsoft Edge</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/enable-and-disable-cookies-website-preferences" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Mozilla Firefox</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Types of Cookies We Use</h2>
  <h3>5.1. Essential Cookies (Strictly Necessary)</h3>
  <p>
    These are required for the Site to function (e.g., security, network management, and loading the content). You cannot opt out of these.
  </p>

  <h3>5.2. Analytics / Performance Cookies</h3>
  <p>
    These help us understand how visitors interact with our Site by collecting and reporting information anonymously (e.g., Google Analytics). We use this data to improve our UX and content.
  </p>

  <h3>5.3. Marketing / Advertising Cookies</h3>
  <p>
    These track visitors across websites to display relevant ads and measure the efficiency of marketing campaigns (e.g., LinkedIn Insights, Google Ads).
  </p>

